==Scottish Gaelic==

===Verb===
'''tha'''

#the positive present-tense form of the copula, the verb "to be." It is used to connect a noun to an adjective, pronoun, or verbal noun.
#*''Tha mi pòsda.'' (I'm married.)
#*''Tha mi à Colbhasa.'' (I am from Colonsay.)
#*''Tha mi a' smaoineachadh gu bheil.'' (lit. I am at thinking so.)

